HAPPY NEW YEAR!! 

I’ve taken some time off social media recently, mainly to really focus in on what it is I want to achieve this year. I am excited with what’s ahead in all aspects of my life. So here’s to a good one 🙌. I wish you all a healthy and happy 2023 🤛. Here’s a few pics of some moments captured from 2022.

Excited to be getting closer to the start of the 2023 British Superbike season, we begin testing in March for the official BSB tests and then first race weekend early April. 

*Exciting Opportunity*

I have some availability to take on new sponsors/partners, there are a number of ways of working together including corporate hospitality where you can bring clients, staff or just yourself, the hospitality is provided through my team, one of, if not the best hospitality in the paddock with the best staff, i'm sure I have friends/associates on here who can vouch for that!! Branding opportunities on my crash helmet and limited space on leathers. Brand ambassador roles and social media targeted marketing. There are budgets to suit all size businesses, so if you think you might be interested please email me to find out more.

db83buchan@gmail.com

Many thanks, 
Danny

Shame the crash brought a premature end to the weekend. I still have no definitive answers on what I have injured as very contradicting results, I will update as and when I know, I will say I’m relatively ok, I’m home and in recovery mode getting ready for round 2. Was lovely to see so many fans and thank you all for your concerns, it’s an occupational hazard sometimes 😂.

What can I say about this guy, what an inspiration to not only the young racers out there but even me at 30 years old. NEVER GIVE UP. This guy has grafted his tits off for so many years, constantly battling off nay sayers and critics slagging him off, he’s never been handed one thing on a plate, people probably are quick to judge and say he’s come from money because he’s now in GP, he hasn’t! His parents had to graft double hard to provide for him, get sponsors each year to be able to race. But what a journey, what a story, even when people close stopped believing, his real circle never did and most importantly he never did, @jakedixonracing - you are the fucking man! I can’t wait to see you get to moto gp. Even though you’re my mate you’ve inspired me and i know for a fact the youngsters out there will hear your story and I’m sure you will be the reason many start and become world champs in the future. @sarahdixon_ you probs need a triple heart bypass after this but what s women, you two have been through so much I can honestly say im so happy to see team Dixon succeeding. If we can’t big our mates up who can we big up. ❤️

So gutted to crash out of P5 in yesterdays race. I got a good start and was sat behind Tommy in P5 relaxed and being conservative with the tyre as I knew he was waiting for the race to progress before he moved forward which made my plan simple, try and go forward when he goes! I came out of T4 into T5 and knew I was wide, got on the dirty part of the track and when I got on the gas it high-sided me over the front.  Can’t say I’m enjoying the sport at the moment if I’m honest but it’s the chosen path, no broken bones thankfully just smashed to pieces and bruised. Thanks for the well wishes x

Don’t even know where to start, out for another race weekend to due to a crash in FP1 which has resulted in a concussion. Wasn’t a big crash however landed funny and ended up bashing the head. Thank you to the amazing BSB medics who again looked after me. Sorry to my team and sponsors, I will be resting this week and getting more scans in the coming week to assess the best way to move forward. Gutted to say the least, felt good in the evening test session and up until the crash felt comfortable and ended the session P6 but in the ambulance 🤦‍♂️🤷‍♂️

Thank you everyone for the messages and comments. 👍
Took some time off the socials last week or so, here’s a dump of what I have been doing ❤️🙌

First and foremost I want to thank my guys at @synetiqbmw and BMW for the last 3 years, we have had ups and downs and everything in between. We’ve won races and we’ve had many podiums so I’d say it was a successful time! This season has tested us all and for that reason I really wanted to get back on at the last 2 rounds and end this season with a couple of good rounds to say f@&k you 2023 😂 but it’s not to be!

Sadly the doc has ruled me out of the last 2 rounds due to the concussions suffered so it means I’ll be spectating and not riding. It sucks massively but health is paramount and especially the brain, it’s already small so got to look after it 😂😂😂. I will be resting the brain for a while. Thank you all for the support and kind words. If you’re lucky you might soon find out what my plans are for 2024. I will be back on the BSB grid and I can’t wait. So keep your eyes peeled 👀

Thank you to my loyal sponsors below who have continued to support me. It means alot!!!

Well 2023, I am thankful you happened. I learnt so much about my character this year, i learnt so much about resilience. I believe my kids will have learnt a lot being involved and living/seeing what we as a family overcome. I learnt so much about the people closest to me and how the true souls dragged me out of some shit times. I am grateful for my family and friends.

One day I will tell the story of 2023 and how dark it was for me and I overcome such a horrid period of my life, and I don’t just mean my racing life. I mean in life LIFE. But that time isn’t now. Right now I’m grateful and enjoying it. 

Looking back at 23, I wouldn’t of been able to have gotten through it without @steffy_x you are my true soulmate, this shit you’ve dealt with year, the crashes, the down days, the busy days. I am eternally grateful for you. I believe whatever life throws at us we will overcome, I love you xx

All I would say is please, if you are struggling, just keep fucking going, there is a light at the end of the tunnel you just have to keep going until you see it, however long that takes don’t give up. Promise yourself that and promise your loved ones that. I’m not posting for sympathy, I’m posting because I’m real, I’m posting because not everything on here is all it’s made out to be, if one person reads this and is in a dark dark place and understands so many people are struggling and smiling through it and can manage to overcome their own demons, I’ll be so happy.

I am so excited for 2024 in many ways. Thank you everyone for your support.  Here’s some of my fav pics of 23, I have 100s more but can only share 10 😂.
